<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/7051533-michael"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1322332389i/7051533._UY100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/7051533-michael">Michael</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">No - Thomas is who Aue could be if he was unhindered by his own thoughts and intellect. Thomas is a social butterfly navigating the world that way whi<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">No - Thomas is who Aue could be if he was unhindered by his own thoughts and intellect. Thomas is a social butterfly navigating the world that way while Aue fails at understanding bureaucracy and is limited thusly. It's more of a point/counterpoint than an alter ego. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
